Do’s in Responsible Social Media Usage:
  Audit Your Privacy Settings Regularly, to check who can view your personal posts.
  Use A Professional Bio,  to ensure a credible Identity.
  Share Academic and Extracurricular Achievements.
  Think before Tagging.
  Verify Information.
Don’ts in Responsible Social Media Usage:
  Post Confidential Information, like Student ID, Home Address, etc.
  Engage In Online Arguments, use of inflammatory Language can and will be permanently tied to your name.
  Plagiarize or Steal other’s Intellectual Property.
  Post Content Depicting Illegal Acts.
  Vent about Employer, Professors or Any such Authority.
